Rights activist Deji Adeyanju has obtained a First Class in Law. He announced this on his Twitter handle on Tuesday. Adeyanju shared his statement of results from Baze University, Abuja, showing he graduated with a First Class.   Fans think Rihanna may be expecting twins     Six Nigerian entertainers with medical degrees     Yomi Fabiyi visits ailing Kemi Afolabi   The convener of CONCERNED NIGERIANS expressed gratitude to God for the feat. According to him, it wasn’t an easy ride getting to this point as he had to keep reinventing himself. He tweeted: “To God alone be the glory. I suffered so much to get here. I have always known the law as someone who went through several criminal & civil trials but I had to unlearn to learn many things. Thank you, Lord.”